<br>
I see it as a negative that here are thousands of super high-level characters all over the darn place. (And yes, I’m probably talking about most of the users of this board.)<br>
<br>
How does this affect new players? I’ll give some observations with pros and cons:<br>
<br>
1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Half of just about every group I join are twinks.  (Somebody’s super twinked 2nd, 3rd, or 4th character.)<br>
Positive – Groups tear up the mobs, great exp, plus the twinks never loot <br>
Negative - When casters and rogues have “almost” more HP’s or AC than the tank (me) at the same level, that’s a problem. . It’s not much fun getting all the loot when the rest of the group laughingly calls it all “junk”.<br>
<br>
2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Farmers EVERYWHERE. <br>
Pros – Tradeskill materials are in surplus in bazaar.<br>
Cons - Last night there were 3 level 60+ groups in DSP alone – hoppers (hides) and tribals (acrylia) were totally camped by these groups. So people of the “appropriate” level for these zones &amp; mobs couldn’t hunt them, or join a group that was.<br>
 <br>
3)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lots of good equipment is being won by raids/camps and then sold in bazaar. <br>
Pros – Great gear at bargain prices <br>
Cons - Prices are so low, on what I’m sure used to be considered good to great gear that it makes many of the mid level quests a waste of time. (Unless you do quests purely for the fun and not the reward).<br>
 <br>
4)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Tons of high level tradecrafters <br>
Pros – Once again great gear at bargain prices<br>
Cons - Flooding the market with low priced goods. It’s funny, but since they don’t need the money, the masters are often pricing their goods below cost. And when they have 8 of each item for sale, newer sellers don’t have much of a chance to sell something.<br>
<br>
5)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Drive-Thru Buffs or Buffs-While-U-Wait<br>
Pros – Pre-patch, KEI &amp; amazing buffs for everyone (donations)<br>
Cons – Crack addicts everywhere. Super twinks who’ve been buffed to the moon by their uber-guild in my groups.  Game balance anyone ?<br>
<br>
Don’t get me wrong. I believe all your high level folks have every right to do all the farming &amp; twinking you want. You’ve invested the time and deserve all the rewards that come with your achievements. I’m just saying that from a newer players standpoint, jumping into the game now, there are drawbacks.  Moving to EQII will remove many of them.<br>
<br>
And don’t give me the “if you don’t like it quit” line.  Even with the zillions of Barons and Baroness’s running around EQ it’s still a fantastic game. I just realize how much better it might be if I’d been in that first wave of players. No eqatlas, no eqtraders, no Lucy, no Allakhazam, etc.<br>
<br>
Yes, I’m sure EQII will be buggy, Yes, I’m sure the depth of content will be much shallower than EQ at first, and Yes, I’m sure I’ll get frustrated as all hell at getting lost all the time.  But at the same time, I’m pretty sure I’ll love it. <br>
<br>
Plus, since us noobs haven't invested all the years you all have in EQ, the move will be much more painless.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why all of a sudden did it get so quiet......&quot;<br>
/looks around at the great noob exodus<br>
